snippet: Negotiators in the U.S. Congress on Monday unveiled a $1.1 trillion spending bill that aims to prevent another government shutdown while boosting funding levels slightly for military and domestic programs - but not for "Obamacare" health reforms....

headline.print_headline: U.S. Lawmakers Unveil $1.1 Trillion Spending Bill, No Obamacare Increase
headline.main: U.S. Lawmakers Unveil $1.1 Trillion Spending Bill, No Obamacare Increase

lead_paragraph: Negotiators in the U.S. Congress on Monday unveiled a $1.1 trillion spending bill that aims to prevent another government shutdown while boosting funding levels slightly for military and domestic programs - but not for "Obamacare" health reforms.
